episodes.title: Habeas Tortoise
episodes.plot: After humiliating himself at a town meeting, Homer looks for acceptance in an internet group on the hunt for a missing tortoise and finds something much more sinister.

episodes.title: One Angry Lisa
episodes.plot: Lisa gets called for jury duty, while Marge becomes obsessed with her exercise bike.

episodes.title: Lisa the Boy Scout
episodes.plot: The show is hijacked by cyber terrorists.

episodes.title: The King of Nice
episodes.plot: Marge gets a job as a segment producer on Krusty's new talk show, which she soon realizes is a never-ending nightmare.

episodes.title: Not It
episodes.plot: Young Homer and his friends are terrorized by a killer clown in a special Treehouse of Horror presentation spoofing Stephen King's "It".

episodes.title: Treehouse of Horror XXXIII
episodes.plot: In the 33rd annual Halloween special, Marge's resentment takes a monstrous form, Lisa tries to save the planet through murder, and Homer realizes that he's not the man he thought he was.

episodes.title: From Beer to Paternity
episodes.plot: Homer and Duffman go on a road trip with Lisa that threatens to expose Homer's bad parenting after he becomes Duffman's girl-dad hero.

episodes.title: Step Brother from the Same Planet
episodes.plot: Homer is filled with rage and resentment when Grampa becomes a stepfather to his girlfriend's son; Lisa and Bart throw the ultimate slumber party.

episodes.title: When Nelson Met Lisa
episodes.plot: Lisa and Nelson become an unlikely couple in the future.

episodes.title: Game Done Changed
episodes.plot: Bart ropes Principal Skinner into his scheme to make off a glitch in an online game; Marge and Maggie discover paradise.

episodes.title: Top Goon
episodes.plot: Moe coaches Bart's hockey team and recruits the world's greatest brawlers to teach Nelson the art of hockey goonery.

episodes.title: My Life as a Vlog
episodes.plot: The rise and fall of the Simpson Family Vlog is told through a series of recommended YouTube videos.

episodes.title: The Many Saints of Springfield
episodes.plot: Ned goes into business with the Springfield mafia.

episodes.title: Carl Carlson Rides Again
episodes.plot: Carl discovers the origins of a mysterious rodeo buckle tied to his identity when he's smitten with a beautiful black woman.

episodes.title: Bartless
episodes.plot: Homer and Marge imagine a world where Bart isn't a Simpson after his latest prank causes chaos at Springfield Elementary.

episodes.title: Hostile Kirk Place
episodes.plot: Kirk goes on a crusade to censor and control the school curriculum in response to a history lesson that paints one of his ancestors in a bad light and Homer comes along for fun and profit.

episodes.title: Pin Gal
episodes.plot: Jacques returns to coach Marge for a bowling tournament.

episodes.title: Fan-ily Feud
episodes.plot: Homer publicly disparages a pop singer and faces the wrath of her vengeful fans.

episodes.title: Write Off This Episode
episodes.plot: Marge is seduced by the money and prestige of Big Charity fundraising when she and Lisa launch a charity together.

episodes.title: The Very Hungry Caterpillars
episodes.plot: The Simpsons are forced to spend time with each other in lockdown when a plague of insects shuts down Springfield.

episodes.title: Clown v. Board of Education
episodes.plot: Krusty opens a school for clowning, which becomes the most successful thing he's ever done.

episodes.title: Homer's Adventures Through the Windshield Glass
episodes.plot: Time stands still for Homer when he flies through his windshield after crashing his car and as his life flashes before his eyes, a magical friend helps him uncover the truth about his marriage.
